# IMU Orientation Estimation Using Madgwick Filter

## 1. Project Scope

This project uses an IMU mounted on the head to estimate head orientation during BPPV-related diagnostic and treatment manoeuvres.

The current baseline orientation estimator is the Madgwick IMU filter provided by the supervisor. The IMU provides:

- 3-axis accelerometer data
- 3-axis gyroscope data

The filter outputs:

- unit quaternion: `qw, qx, qy, qz`
- Euler angles: `roll, pitch, yaw`
- estimated gravity vector
- estimated user/linear acceleration

The current implementation is IMU-only. Therefore, roll and pitch can be corrected using the gravity direction measured by the accelerometer, but yaw/heading is expected to drift over time because no magnetometer or external heading reference is used.

The purpose of this stage is not yet to diagnose BPPV directly. Instead, the objective is to build a reliable orientation-estimation pipeline that can track and verify head positions during manoeuvres such as Dix-Hallpike and Epley.

---

## 2. Data Format

The Arduino/XIAO Seeed board streams raw IMU data over serial in the following format:

```text
timestamp_ms, ax, ay, az, gx, gy, gz